Description: The University of North Alabama’s Master of Accountancy (MAcc) program is a 30-credit hour graduate business program that will prepare students for a career in accounting. Graduates with an MAcc degree possess the technical skills and broad business perspective needed for a successful career. Students who graduate with their MAcc degree from UNA meet the educational requirements to sit for the CPA exam in the state of Alabama. The UNA MAcc program has consistently ranked as one of the top programs by various publications. The accounting program at UNA is known throughout the region for its quality and for the success of its graduates. Our program faculty are highly qualified, with a majority holding a doctorate degree and a CPA certification. They offer a diverse range of expertise and experience and are passionate about students’ professional development.
Accredidation: The Master of Accountancy program has separate accounting accreditation through AACSB International—The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business. UNA is one of only 194 universities in the world to hold this prestigious accreditation. AACSB represents the highest standard of achievement for business schools worldwide.

ProgramName: Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner Cert
Description: The Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions offers post-graduate APRN certificate programs for nurses who have an earned Master of Science in Nursing (MSN) or Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP) degree and wish to obtain an additional specialty certification as a Nurse Practitioner. The certificates are designed to be completed in four to five semesters of part-time study. Post-Graduate APRN Certificate students are accepted for fall and spring admission.
Accredidation: The baccalaureate degree program in nursing, master's degree program in nursing, and post-graduate APRN certificate program at the University of North Alabama are accredited by the Commission on Collegiate Nursing Education (http://www.ccneaccreditation.org).

ProgramName: Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner MSN
EnglishScore: All applicants whose native language is not English must demonstrate English proficiency through the submission of a satisfactory score on the Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL), International English Language Testing System (IELTS), Pearson Test of English (PTE) Academic, or Duolingo. The following are the minimum score requirements for admission to a degree program: TOEFL- 79 iBT (internet-based test) or 550 PBT (paper-based test), IELTS- an overall band score of 6.0, PTE Academic- a score of 54, or Duolingo - a score of 105. Students may also meet the English proficiency requirement by completion of the University of North Alabama's intensive English Program (ELS) with a certificate of completion for level 112.
Requirements: Unconditional admission to the MSN program may be granted to applicants who meet the following criteria: Hold a Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree from a nationally accredited program (ACEN or CCNE). Have a minimum overall undergraduate GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale or a 3.0 on the last 60 hours of undergraduate coursework. Hold an unencumbered registered nurse license in the state where clinical experiences will be completed. Have completed an undergraduate or graduate statistics course with a grade of C or better. Submit a completed application to the Office of Graduate Admissions. Provide evidence of a minimum of one year of recent clinical experience as a Registered Nurse in an acute care setting. This will be verified by the employing agency. Submission of three recommendation forms (from a current or former supervisor, a peer, and a former faculty member if possible). Submit a resume. Submit a professional goal statement. Applicants may be required to participate in an interview.
Department: Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions
Description: The Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner (AGACNP) track is designed to prepare students for advanced practice nursing with acutely ill adult and gerontology patients. Graduates are educated to provide a spectrum of care from disease prevention to acute and critical care management. The AGACNP is prepared to care for patients in intensive care units, emergency departments, specialty labs (e.g., cardiac catheterization, electrophysiology), specialty clinics (e.g., cardiology, pulmonology) and hospitalist/intensivist services. The AGACNP is a member of the multi-disciplinary healthcare team and practices in collaboration with physicians and other healthcare providers. Graduates are eligible to take the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC) or the American Association of Critical Care Nurses (AACN) Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner certification examinations.
Accredidation: The baccalaureate degree program in nursing, master's degree program in nursing, and post-graduate APRN certificate program at the University of North Alabama are accredited by the Commission on Collegiate Nursing Education (http://www.ccneaccreditation.org).

ProgramName: Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner Cert
EnglishScore: Applicants whose native language is not English must submit one of the following to meet the English proficiency requirement: TOEFL - Minimum score of 79 (IBT) or 550 (PBT), IELTS - Minimum score of 6.0, PTE - Minimum score of 54, Duolingo - Minimum score of 110, or ELS - Completion of ELS Level 112.
Requirements: Unconditional admission to the graduate program at UNA. A Master of Science in Nursing from a regionally accredited institution and a nationally accredited nursing program (ACEN or CCNE). A current, unencumbered registered nurse license in the state where clinical experiences will be completed. A minimum of one year of direct patient care experience as a registered nurse. A minimum cumulative GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale on all previous academic work. Successful completion of a 3-credit hour undergraduate or graduate-level statistics course with a grade of C or better. Submission of the following documents to the Office of Graduate Admissions: Official transcripts from all postsecondary institutions attended, Three letters of professional reference attesting to the applicant’s potential for graduate study, A curriculum vitae or resume, A personal statement/essay, Copy of RN license. Submission of a completed background check. Submission of a completed drug screen.
Department: Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions
Description: The Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner Certificate (AGPCNP) track at UNA prepares graduates to provide primary health care for adults across the lifespan from adolescence through senescence. The curriculum emphasizes health promotion and maintenance, and the diagnosis and management of common acute and chronic health problems. Upon completion of the program, graduates will be eligible to seek certification as an Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner through the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC) or the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners (AANP).
Accredidation: The baccalaureate degree program in nursing, master's degree program in nursing, and post-graduate APRN certificate programs at the University of North Alabama are accredited by the Commission on Collegiate Nursing Education (http://www.ccneaccreditation.org).

ProgramName: Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner MSN
EnglishScore: Applicants whose native language is not English must provide evidence of proficiency in the English language. This can be met by submitting one of the following official test scores: TOEFL (Test of English as a Foreign Language), IELTS (International English Language Testing System), PTE (Pearson Test of English Academic), Duolingo, or by successful completion of ELS Language Center's Level 112.
Requirements: Application to the MSN program is a two-part process. Applicants must first apply to the UNA Office of Graduate Admissions. Following application to the University, applicants must complete the Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions MSN Program Application. Requirements for the Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions MSN Program application include: a current resume or curriculum vitae; a statement of purpose (500-750 words) describing professional goals and motivation for graduate study; three (3) letters of recommendation; official transcripts from all post-secondary institutions attended; a current, unencumbered registered nurse license in the state where clinical experiences will occur; a Baccalaureate degree in nursing (BSN) from a regionally accredited institution with ACEN or CCNE program accreditation; an undergraduate GPA of 3.0 or greater on a 4.0 scale; a statistics course with a grade of C or better; and evidence of one year full-time nursing experience as a registered nurse prior to the first clinical course.
Department: Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions
Description: The adult-gerontology primary care nurse practitioner track is a hybrid program designed to prepare nurses to provide primary care services to the entire spectrum of adults, including young adults, adults, and older adults. The primary focus of the adult-gerontology primary care nurse practitioner is to provide comprehensive, chronic, and continuous care to patients in a variety of primary care settings. Adult-gerontology primary care nurse practitioners are educated to provide a broad range of primary care services that includes performing health assessments, ordering, performing, and interpreting diagnostic tests, and prescribing medications and other treatments. Upon successful completion of the program of study, graduates will be eligible to take the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC) Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner certification examination or the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners (AANP) Adult-Gerontology Primary Care Nurse Practitioner certification examination. Upon successful completion of the certification exam, graduates will be eligible for licensure in their state of residence. Graduates who apply for initial licensure in a compact state, or who change their primary state of residence to a compact state, may be eligible for a multistate license. Additionally, graduates who live in and practice in compact states may be eligible for a multistate license.
Accredidation: The baccalaureate degree program in nursing, master's degree program in nursing, and post-graduate APRN certificate program at the University of North Alabama are accredited by the Commission on Collegiate Nursing Education (http://www.ccneaccreditation.org).

EnglishScore: Applicants must meet one of the following requirements: TOEFL score of 79 (IBT), 550 (PBT), or 213 (CBT); IELTS score of 6.0; PTE score of 54; Duolingo score of 110; or completion of ELS level 112 with a 2.5 GPA.
Requirements: Admission to the program is based on the student’s undergraduate record and other indicators of aptitude for graduate study. Applicants must have a bachelor’s degree from an accredited institution. Applicants must submit a completed application for admission to graduate study. Applicants must have official transcripts from each institution attended sent directly to the Office of Graduate Admissions. Applicants must have an overall undergraduate grade point average of at least 2.75 on a 4.00 scale. Applicants with an overall undergraduate grade point average of 2.50 to 2.74 on a 4.00 scale will be considered for conditional admission. A formal application to the M.A. in Professional Communication program, statement of purpose, and three letters of recommendation must be submitted to the Department of Communication Graduate Coordinator.

EnglishScore: Applicants from countries where English is not the native language must submit proof of English language proficiency. Accepted options include: a minimum score of 79 on the TOEFL iBT (or 550 on the PBT), a minimum score of 6.0 on the IELTS, a minimum score of 54 on the PTE, a minimum score of 100 on the Duolingo English Test, or completion of Level 112 of the ELS Language Center.
Requirements: A bachelor's degree from a regionally accredited institution with at least a 3.0 GPA in the last 60 semester hours of undergraduate work. At least 18 hours of previous undergraduate anthropology coursework with a grade of C or better. A formal application to the Graduate School. Official transcripts from each institution attended. A statement of purpose of at least 500 words describing the applicant’s research interests, professional goals, and reasons for pursuing a master’s degree in anthropology at UNA. Three letters of recommendation submitted via the online application system from individuals qualified to judge the applicant's potential for success in a graduate program. At least two letters should be from former professors. A writing sample demonstrating the applicant's ability to conduct research and write a scholarly paper. This should be a research paper written for a previous course. There is no minimum or maximum word count.
Department: College of Arts, Sciences, and Engineering
Description: The Master of Arts in Anthropology with a concentration in Applied Biological Anthropology at the University of North Alabama (UNA) offers a unique and comprehensive educational experience for students interested in the practical application of biological anthropology. This program is designed to provide students with a strong theoretical foundation in biological anthropology, combined with hands-on training in research methods and techniques that can be applied to real-world problems. The curriculum focuses on areas such as human osteology, forensic anthropology, bioarchaeology, primatology, and human biology, preparing students for careers in academia, government agencies, museums, and the private sector.
ScholarshipType: Academic scholarships, Graduate Assistantships, Fellowships, International Student Scholarships

Requirements: Admission into the program will be based on approval from the geology certificate committee. For non-degree seeking students, the University of North Alabama’s requirements for undergraduate and graduate admissions must be met. Current UNA students who wish to earn the certificate should contact Dr. M. Taylor to fill out an application form for program admission. Contact information is on the right side of this page. Students working on the Certificate in Applied Carbonate Geology are expected to maintain a minimum GPA of 3.0 in courses in the certificate program.
Description: The Certificate in Applied Carbonate Geology focuses on the depositional and diagenetic aspects of carbonate rocks and the unique challenges these present to geologists. The certificate provides students with an understanding of modern carbonate depositional environments, petrographic techniques for carbonate rock characterization and diagenesis, and experience in subsurface geologic methods. Carbonate rocks are important hosts of oil and natural gas, groundwater, and Mississippi-Valley type ore deposits. In addition, the unique properties of carbonate rocks have important implications for CO2 sequestration and other environmental geology applications. This certificate is designed to be completed in one year and requires 12 graduate credit hours.

EnglishScore: Applicants whose native language is not English must provide proof of English proficiency by one of the following: TOEFL iBT score of 79, IELTS score of 6.0, PTE score of 54, Duolingo English Test score of 105, or successful completion of ELS Level 112.
Requirements: Hold a masters or educational specialist degree from an accredited institution. A cumulative GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale on all graduate coursework. Submit an application to the Office of Graduate Admissions. Submit a professional resume or curriculum vitae. Submit official transcripts from all institutions attended. Submit three recommendations from school administrators or supervisors using the Leadership Disposition form. Submit a writing sample that responds to a provided prompt. Instructions on how to complete the writing sample will be sent after the application is submitted. Complete an admissions interview.
Description: The Executive Doctorate of Business Administration (EDBA) at the University of North Alabama is a professional doctoral program for executives and senior managers who want to advance their knowledge, skills, and abilities to the highest level. The EDBA is designed for working professionals who desire to distinguish themselves as thought leaders in their respective fields. The EDBA curriculum is designed to produce scholar-practitioners who can develop and lead evidence-based management and data-driven decision making. EDBA graduates will be equipped to advance their careers to C-suite and other upper-level management positions in both the for-profit and non-profit sectors. In addition, EDBA graduates will be qualified to teach in business programs at most universities.
Accredidation: The University of North Alabama Sanders College of Business and Technology is accredited by AACSB International - The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business.

Requirements: Applicants for admission to the Applied Learning Sciences, Ed.D. program should submit the following to the Office of Graduate Admissions: Completed UNA Graduate Application; Official transcripts from all colleges/universities attended, including an official transcript that shows a master's degree was conferred from a regionally accredited institution; Three letters of recommendation; A current résumé; A writing sample: An academic paper or professional report which demonstrates the applicant’s potential for success in a doctoral program; A statement of purpose that includes a description of the applicant’s professional goals, research interests, and a rationale for why the applicant is a strong candidate for the Applied Learning Sciences, Ed.D. program; and A minimum GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale on all graduate-level coursework. A screening interview may be required.
Department: College of Education and Human Sciences
Concentration: Instructional Design and Technology, Literacy, Teacher Leader
Description: The online Doctor of Education in Applied Learning Sciences from the University of North Alabama has been designed for educators and other professionals who want to understand learning and teaching from an evidence-based perspective. This doctoral program is designed to provide you with a broad understanding of learning sciences while developing your expertise through one of our three concentrations. Our Applied Learning Sciences doctoral degree will equip you with a nuanced view of education that includes the historical context for today’s educational landscape, the sociological and cultural factors that affect learning, the psychological perspectives that inform educational research, and the policies that shape educational practices.
Accredidation: The University of North Alabama is accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools Commission on Colleges (SACSCOC) to award bachelor's, master's, education specialist, and doctoral degrees. The College of Education and Human Sciences is also accredited by the Council for the Accreditation of Educator Preparation (CAEP).

EnglishScore: Students from non-English speaking countries must provide proof of English proficiency. This can be met by providing an official score report from one of the following: a minimum score of 525 on the paper-based (PBT) or 70 on the Internet-based (iBT) TOEFL, a minimum score of 6.0 on the IELTS, a minimum score of 54 on the PTE (Pearson Test of English) Academic, a minimum score of 100 on the Duolingo test, or successful completion of Level 112 of the ELS Language Centers Intensive Program.
Requirements:
Admission to the Applied Physiology Program is based upon the student’s academic background, professional experience, recommendations, and personal statement. In order to be considered for admission, applicants must satisfy the general requirements for admission to graduate study and the Department of Kinesiology.

1. Complete an application to the Graduate Studies Office.
2. Submit three letters of recommendation to the Department of Kinesiology.
3. Provide a written essay that outlines reasons for wanting to obtain a graduate degree in Applied Physiology.
4. Minimum cumulative grade point average (GPA) of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale on all undergraduate coursework.
5. A cumulative grade point average (GPA) of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale on all graduate coursework from a regionally accredited university.
6. Students with a GPA of less than 3.0 must score at the 40th percentile or above on the GRE General Test (verbal and quantitative) to be considered for admission.
7. All students must submit GRE General Test Scores.
Department: College of Education and Human Sciences
Description: The Master of Science in Education with a concentration in Applied Physiology is designed for students seeking advanced knowledge and skills in exercise physiology. The curriculum integrates physiological and anatomical principles with the study of human movement. Through coursework, laboratory experiences, and research, students gain a comprehensive understanding of how the body responds and adapts to exercise. This program prepares graduates for careers in clinical settings, corporate wellness, strength and conditioning, research, and for further doctoral studies. Students will have the opportunity to work closely with faculty on research projects and gain hands-on experience in our state-of-the-art laboratories.

EnglishScore: Proficiency in English must be demonstrated by one of the following: Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) with a minimum score of 540 (paper-based), or 207 (computer-based), or 76 (Internet-based); International English Language Testing System (IELTS) with a minimum score of 6.0; Pearson Test of English (PTE) with a minimum score of 54; ELS Language Centers Level 112 with a grade of B (2.5) or higher; Duolingo English Test with a minimum score of 100. An applicant is exempt from the English proficiency requirement if they have earned a baccalaureate degree from a regionally accredited U.S. institution of higher education or the equivalent from a country on the English Proficiency Waiver list.
Department: College of Arts, Sciences, and Engineering
Description: The MPS in Applied GIS concentration provides students with a solid foundation in geospatial technologies including Geographic Information Systems (GIS), Remote Sensing, Global Positioning Systems (GPS), and related technologies (e.g., mobile mapping, web-based mapping). The purpose of this concentration is to provide specialized training in geospatial technologies that leads to career advancement for students from a broad range of academic and professional backgrounds. The program curriculum is designed to balance theoretical and applied concepts, with a strong focus on project based learning. Students can expect to learn the functional and analytical aspects of GIS and other geospatial technologies, which include the collection, management, analysis, and dissemination of geospatial information. The curriculum emphasizes the application of geospatial technologies to real-world problems. Students in this concentration are expected to demonstrate knowledge and mastery of geospatial technologies by completing a capstone project that is selected by the student with approval from the Department of Geography Graduate Coordinator. The capstone experience allows students the opportunity to integrate their knowledge by applying geospatial technologies to a variety of applications including, but not limited to, environmental management, urban and regional planning, and economic development. The capstone provides a bridge between graduate study and a professional career, and its completion demonstrates a student’s mastery of geospatial concepts, ability to conduct independent research, and make a significant contribution to the geospatial technology field as a whole.

EnglishScore: In addition to the specific requirements for the program to which an applicant is seeking admission, international students must submit one of the following as evidence of English proficiency: Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) with a minimum score of 500 on the paper-based test (PBT) or 61 on the Internet-based test (iBT); International English Language Testing System (IELTS) with a minimum score of 5.5; Pearson Test of English (PTE) Academic with a minimum score of 46; Duolingo with a minimum score of 95; Successful completion of the English Language Services (ELS) language program, Level 112.
Description: The Aquaculture concentration of the Master of Professional Studies program is designed to provide graduate training in aquaculture for students whose primary career interests are in the professions of government, business, and industry, as opposed to research and teaching. The curriculum is interdisciplinary, but its foundation rests on the biological sciences of fisheries, aquatic ecology, water quality, nutrition, physiology, and genetics. Applied fields in business are also integral parts of the curriculum, providing students with knowledge and skill in accounting, marketing,management, and economics. Coursework and professional experience are integrated to ensure students receive the practical experience necessary to be successful in the aquaculture industry.

Requirements: A bachelor’s degree from a regionally accredited institution with an undergraduate GPA of 2.75 or higher on a 4.0 scale. Official transcripts from all institutions attended. A resume or curriculum vitae. A statement of purpose. Three letters of recommendation. International students whose native language is not English must submit a satisfactory score on the Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL), International English Language Testing System (IELTS), or Duolingo.
Department: College of Arts, Sciences, and Engineering
Concentration: Building Structures, Building Mechanical Systems, or Building Enclosure Systems
Description: Architectural Engineering is the application of engineering principles and technology to building design and construction. The purpose of this program is to provide the knowledge and skills necessary to design building systems. Students can specialize in one of three areas: Building Structures, Building Mechanical Systems, or Building Enclosure Systems. Graduates of this program may go on to careers in consulting engineering firms, construction companies, building equipment manufacturers, facility management companies or government agencies.

EnglishScore: All applicants whose native language is not English are required to demonstrate English proficiency by submitting one of the following: TOEFL: Minimum score of 79 iBT (internet-based) or 550 PBT (paper-based); IELTS: Minimum score of 6.0; PTE: Minimum score of 54; Duolingo English Test: Minimum score of 105; or successful completion of the University of North Alabama’s English as a Second Language (ESL) Program.
Requirements:
In addition to meeting the university admission requirements for graduate studies, the applicant must:
1. Submit a portfolio of 10-20 images of previous undergraduate or professional work. The portfolio should include samples of hand-drawing, two- and three-dimensional design, and may include architectural drawings, paintings, prints, photographs, and/or sculpture.
2. Submit a 250-word statement of purpose.
3. Submit a resume.
4. Complete a formal interview with program faculty.
Portfolios, resumes, and statements of purpose should be uploaded through the Graduate Admissions application portal.
Description: The University of North Alabama, in partnership with the Institute of Classical Architecture & Art (ICAA), offers a graduate-level Certificate in Classical Architecture. This 15-credit hour certificate program provides students with a working knowledge of classical architectural design. The coursework offers an introduction to the classical orders, the literature of classical architecture, proportion, and the study of precedent, and offers one of two concentrations in either architectural design or architectural history & theory.

EnglishScore: Applicants whose native language is not English must submit evidence of English proficiency. This can be met by providing an acceptable score on the TOEFL (minimum 61 iBT or 500 PBT), IELTS (minimum 5.5), PTE Academic (minimum 46), or Duolingo English Test (minimum 90). Successful completion of ELS Language Centers Level 112 is also accepted.
Department: College of Arts, Sciences, and Engineering
Description: The online Certificate in Artist Development is a 12-credit hour undergraduate certificate program for non-degree-seeking students that can be completed in two semesters. It is designed to equip aspiring artists, songwriters, producers, and entrepreneurs with foundational creative and technical skills and essential knowledge for pursuing a career in today’s music business and recording industries.
Accredidation: All programs in the Department of Visual Arts and Design are accredited by the National Association of Schools of Art and Design (NASAD).

EnglishScore: Applicants from countries where English is not the native language must submit proof of English proficiency. This can be done by providing an official score report from one of the following: TOEFL iBT (minimum score 79); IELTS (minimum score 6.0); PTE (minimum score 54); Duolingo (minimum score 110); or completion of ELS Level 112.
Requirements: Submit an application for admission to graduate studies at UNA. Submit official transcripts from all post-secondary institutions attended to the UNA Office of Graduate Admissions. Have an earned undergraduate degree from a regionally accredited institution with a minimum cumulative GPA of 2.5 on a 4.0 scale.
Department: College of Education & Human Sciences

EnglishScore: All applicants for graduate admission whose native language is not English are required to submit proof of English proficiency by one of the following methods: TOEFL with a minimum score of 550 on the paper-based test (PBT) or 79 on the internet-based test (iBT), IELTS with a minimum score of 6.0, PTE with a minimum score of 54, Duolingo with a minimum score of 100, or successful completion of the ELS Language Centers Level 112.
Requirements: A bachelor’s degree from a regionally accredited institution. At least a 2.5 GPA (on a 4.0 scale) in undergraduate degree. Completion of the graduate application. Submission of official transcripts from all colleges/universities attended. A statement of purpose of at least 300 words outlining the applicant’s interest in the field and career goals. A curriculum vitae/resume.
Department: College of Arts, Sciences, and Engineering
Description: The Arts Management certificate is a 12-hour online program of study which provides graduate-level coursework for individuals seeking employment in the arts management field. The certificate is appropriate for individuals with bachelor's degrees who wish to enhance their professional profile, practicing arts managers who do not have a formal arts management education, and currently-enrolled graduate students who wish to augment their degree. The courses within the Arts Management certificate may be applied to the Master of Arts in Public History degree with a concentration in Public Humanities.
Accredidation: The Department of Art is accredited by the National Association of Schools of Art and Design (NASAD).
ScholarshipType: Graduate Assistantships, Graduate Council Fellowships, Graduate Student Research Grants

EnglishScore: International applicants must demonstrate English proficiency. UNA accepts a minimum score of 79 on the TOEFL (iBT), 6.0 on the IELTS, 54 on the PTE, or 105 on the Duolingo English Test. Successful completion of the ELS Language Center's Level 112 is also accepted.
Requirements:
To be admitted to the Arts Presenting Fundamentals Certificate program, applicants must meet one of the following requirements:

1. An earned baccalaureate degree from a regionally accredited institution with a cumulative GPA of 2.50 or higher on a 4.0 scale.
2. An earned graduate degree from a regionally accredited institution with a cumulative GPA of 3.0 or higher on a 4.0 scale.

Requirements for Clear Admission

1. Completed application for graduate admission.
2. Official baccalaureate degree transcript from a regionally accredited institution.
3. Official transcripts from all colleges/universities attended.
4. One of the following:
    * Cumulative undergraduate GPA of 2.50 or higher on a 4.00 scale.
    * Cumulative graduate GPA of 3.00 or higher on a 4.00 scale for a completed graduate degree.
Department: College of Arts, Sciences, and Engineering
Description: The Graduate Certificate in Arts Presenting Fundamentals is an 18-hour program designed to provide students with comprehensive knowledge and skills in the field of arts presenting. This program is offered online and provides students with the flexibility to balance their education with their professional and personal commitments. The program focuses on the fundamentals of arts presenting, including programming, marketing, fundraising, financial management, and audience development. Students will learn how to develop and implement successful arts programming, create effective marketing campaigns, and build strong relationships with donors and patrons. The curriculum is designed to provide students with a solid foundation in the principles and practices of arts presenting and to prepare them for careers in a variety of arts organizations, including theaters, museums, galleries, and performing arts centers. The program is ideal for individuals who are currently working in the arts and want to advance their careers, as well as those who are new to the field and want to gain the skills and knowledge needed to succeed.

EnglishScore: English proficiency for international graduate students can be demonstrated by one of the following: TOEFL iBT 79 (or 550 PBT), IELTS 6.0, PTE 54, Duolingo 105, or ELS Level 112.
Requirements:
Admission to the Master of Science in Athletic Training (MSAT) program is competitive and based on academic achievement and other selective criteria. The Athletic Training Program Admissions Committee evaluates applicants on the basis of their potential for success in the program and the profession. To be eligible for consideration for admission into the MSAT program, applicants must meet the following criteria:

- Bachelor’s degree from a regionally accredited institution
- Minimum cumulative undergraduate GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale
- Completion of prerequisite coursework with a C or better in all courses
- Completion of 50 observation hours with an athletic trainer
- Three letters of recommendation
- A written essay (500-1000 words) to include:
    - Your career goals and aspirations
    - Your motivation for pursuing the MSAT at UNA
    - The qualities that you possess which you believe will make you a successful student and athletic trainer
- A current resume that includes:
    - Education
    - Work experience
    - Honors/awards
    - Professional organization membership
    - Volunteer/community service
- Completed Athletic Training Program Technical Standards Form
Description: The Master of Science in Athletic Training (MSAT) at the University of North Alabama is a 5-semester professional graduate program designed to prepare students for a career as an athletic trainer. The MSAT program provides students with the knowledge and skills necessary to become a competent and compassionate healthcare professional. Students will learn how to prevent, diagnose, and treat injuries and illnesses in a variety of settings, including high schools, colleges, professional sports, and clinical settings. Students who successfully complete the MSAT program are eligible to sit for the Board of Certification (BOC) examination.
Accredidation: The Master of Science in Athletic Training program is accredited by the Commission on Accreditation of Athletic Training Education (CAATE), 6850 Austin Center Blvd., Suite 100, Austin, TX 78731-3101. The program has been placed on Probation as of February 19, 2024 by the CAATE.

EnglishScore: One of the following is required for admission to a graduate degree program: Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) iBT score of 79. International English Language Testing System (IELTS) score of 6.0. Pearson Test of English (PTE) Academic score of 54. Duolingo English Test with a score of 110.
MinimumGreScore: A combined verbal and quantitative score of 300 on the Graduate Record Examination (GRE) and an analytical writing score of 3.0 or greater.

Requirements: An official transcript from an accredited institution with a baccalaureate degree with a minimum 2.75 GPA. A resume/CV. A statement of purpose (a one page essay detailing your interest in our MPS program). Two letters of recommendation. A writing sample. (A sample of your writing that demonstrates your ability to write clearly and logically. This can be a paper from a previous course, a professional report, or a similar document). Official transcripts from all colleges and universities attended.
Description: The Master of Professional Studies (MPS) is an online, 30-hour master's degree program for working professionals who wish to further develop their professional skills and knowledge base. This interdisciplinary degree is composed of three parts: a 9-hour professional studies core, a 15-hour primary concentration area, and a 6-hour cognate. The UNA Department of Geography & Environmental Sciences offers the Atmospheric Science concentration for this degree. The program aims to give students a deeper understanding of atmospheric science and its applications to operational meteorology, emergency management, and other environmental-related career fields.

EnglishScore: Applicants whose native language is not English and who have not received a degree from an accredited institution of higher education in the United States must submit a score from the Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL), International English Language Testing System (IELTS), or Pearson Test of English Academic (PTE).
Requirements:
Admission to the graduate program in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology is based on an evaluation by the Biology Graduate Committee of the following application materials:
1. Completed application form with application fee submitted to the Office of Graduate Admissions.
2. Official transcripts of all undergraduate and graduate coursework from accredited institutions.
3. Two letters of recommendation from individuals in professionally relevant fields who can assess the applicant’s potential for success in a graduate program.
4. Statement of purpose that details the applicant’s interest in the MS in Biochemistry and Molecular Biology program at UNA and includes long-term goals.
5. Resume or curriculum vitae.
6. Students for whom English is a second language must meet the University requirements for English proficiency (see University Requirements for Graduate Study).

ProgramName: Biochemistry and Molecular Biology Executive PhD Online
EnglishScore: All students from non-English speaking countries must submit proof of English proficiency. Acceptable proof includes TOEFL (79 iBT or 550 PBT), IELTS (6.0), PTE (54), Duolingo (100), or successful completion of ELS Level 112.
Requirements:
Completed online application and $50 application fee.
Official transcripts from all institutions attended. A master’s degree in a STEM field from a regionally accredited institution is required for admission with a minimum graduate GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale.
An official GRE score report is required for consideration of admission. The GRE may be waived for applicants who have at least five years of significant, professional work experience.
Resume or curriculum vitae (CV).
Statement of Purpose that describes in 500-1000 words the applicant’s interest in the program and reason for pursuing the Executive Ph.D. degree.
Three letters of recommendation submitted through the online application portal from professional or academic references who can attest to the applicant's potential for success in a doctoral program.

Concentration: Thesis Track, Non-Thesis Track, Geospatial Science
Description: The Master of Science (M.S.) degree program in biology will provide graduate students with the opportunity to acquire the knowledge and skills necessary to pursue a career in biology-related fields in government and industry, to teach at the secondary and community college level, or to pursue an advanced degree in a professional or doctoral program. The department is committed to providing graduate students with a hands-on experience in the laboratory and the field through a course of study which integrates teaching and research. The Master of Science in Biology degree program offers two tracks. The thesis track is strongly recommended for students who intend to apply to a doctoral program or seek a research-based job. The non-thesis track is designed for students seeking careers in fields that do not have a significant research emphasis such as secondary school teachers, many government jobs, and some industry jobs. Both thesis and non-thesis students may also complete a concentration in Geospatial Science with an additional 12 credit hours of coursework in that area.

ProgramName: Biomedical Engineering MSBE with emphasis in Medical Physics
EnglishScore: Students must submit proof of English proficiency by providing an official score report for one of the following tests. All test scores are valid for two years from the test date. TOEFL: 79 (IBT) or 550 (PBT), IELTS: 6.0, PTE: 54, Duolingo: 100, ELS: Successful completion of ELS Language Center's Level 112.
Requirements: A bachelor's degree in biomedical engineering or a related engineering field, from a regionally accredited institution, or a bachelor's degree in a STEM field such as physics, chemistry, biology, or mathematics, with a minimum undergraduate GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale. Prerequisite coursework: Differential Equations and Linear Algebra. Application to the UNA Graduate Studies. Official transcripts from all institutions attended. Three letters of recommendation from individuals who can speak to the applicant's academic potential. A Statement of Purpose describing the applicant's research interests and career goals. A current resume or curriculum vitae (CV).
Description: Biomedical Engineering (BME) is a revolutionary and rewarding field. At its core, BME is an interdisciplinary field that applies principles of engineering to the medical field and biological systems. BME professionals are at the forefront of scientific discovery by developing and applying novel technologies to solve complex biological and medical problems that ultimately advance human health and well-being. The Master of Science in Biomedical Engineering (MSBE) program at the University of North Alabama (UNA) prepares students for successful careers in the BME industry, academia, and government, and for advanced-level doctoral studies. MSBE students receive high-quality education and research training from a dedicated faculty in a state-of-the-art research facility in the new UNA STEM building. The MSBE program offers one area of emphasis in medical physics and has a flexible curriculum with thesis and non-thesis options to meet the needs of the students from a variety of backgrounds.
Accredidation: The medical physics emphasis area is accredited by the Commission on Accreditation of Medical Physics Education Programs (CAMPEP).

ProgramName: Biomedical Engineering PhD with emphasis in Medical Physics
Description: This program provides an exciting opportunity for graduate students to pursue doctoral studies in biomedical engineering. The University of Alabama in Huntsville (UAH) and the University of North Alabama (UNA) have joined together to offer a program with an emphasis in medical physics. The UAH Department of Chemical and Materials Engineering and UNA's Department of Physics offer the Joint UAH-UNA Biomedical Engineering PhD with an emphasis in Medical Physics. The program is offered on the UAH campus.

EnglishScore: One of the following must be submitted to meet the English proficiency requirement: Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) score of 79 on iBT (internet based test) or 550 on PBT (paper based test) or higher. International English Language Testing System (IELTS) score of 6.0 or higher. Pearson Test of English (PTE) Academic score of 54 or higher. Duolingo score of 105 or higher. English Language Services (ELS) Level 112.
Requirements:
The requirements for unconditional admission to the Master of Science degree in Biomedical and Health Sciences are:
- A bachelor’s degree from a regionally accredited institution, or the international equivalent, with a minimum cumulative undergraduate GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale.
- A personal statement of 500 words or less.
- Two letters of recommendation from individuals in a supervisory or professional capacity who can attest to the applicant's potential for success in a graduate program.
- Submission of all official transcripts from each post-secondary institution attended.
Department: College of Arts, Sciences, and Engineering
Description: The UNA Department of Biology is pleased to offer a Master of Science (M.S.) degree program in Biomedical Sciences. This program prepares students to meet the demand for highly-skilled, professional scientists in the rapidly-growing health sciences and biotechnology fields. The curriculum for the M.S. in Biomedical Sciences program will allow students to customize their coursework to meet their specific professional goals, including entrance into competitive professional programs (medical, dental, physician assistant, pharmacy, etc.), or for employment in the biomedical or biotechnology industries. The M.S. in Biomedical Sciences program is a one-year, non-thesis program that requires the completion of 30 credit hours.
ScholarshipType: Graduate Assistantships, Graduate Council Scholarships, Departmental Scholarships

Requirements: The following materials should be submitted as part of the application for admission to the PIBS program at UNA: A completed application for admission to graduate study; Official transcripts of all undergraduate and graduate credits from each institution attended; An official report of the General Test of the Graduate Record Examination (GRE) scores from the Educational Testing Service. Scores older than five years will not be accepted; Three letters of recommendation; A personal statement; A resume or curriculum vitae; A completed Department of Biology Graduate Program Application.

Requirements: To be admitted to the MS in Mathematics Program, a student must satisfy the general admission requirements for the Office of Graduate Studies, and be admitted to graduate study at UNA. In addition, the Department of Mathematics requires the applicant to meet the following criteria: 1. An undergraduate major in Mathematics or a related field with at least a 3.0 GPA on a 4.0 scale. 2. Must have completed Calculus I, II, III and at least one additional upper division proof-based course. 3. Students must submit an essay stating their reasons for pursuing a graduate degree in mathematics and their professional goals. 4. Students must submit three letters of recommendation with at least two from university faculty in Mathematics or a closely related discipline.
Department: College of Arts, Sciences, and Engineering
Description: The Biostatistics track is designed for students with an interest in applying statistical methods to the biological sciences, including public health, medicine, and genetics. A graduate with this degree will be able to contribute to research in these areas by analyzing and interpreting data. Our students complete coursework in both the mathematics and biology departments. Coursework includes a one-year sequence in both mathematical statistics and applied statistics. In addition, students have opportunities to collaborate with faculty on research projects as a part of their curriculum.

Requirements: Completed application for admission to graduate study. An official transcript from the college or university that awarded the student's master's degree. Official transcripts from all other colleges and universities attended. A minimum GPA of 3.25 on a 4.0 scale on all previous graduate course work. A statement of purpose (approximately 500-1000 words) that describes the applicant’s research interests and career goals and explains how the PhD in Exercise Science and Health Promotion will help the applicant achieve these goals. The statement of purpose should also identify at least one faculty member in the department with whom the applicant would like to work. Three letters of recommendation from individuals who can attest to the applicant's academic potential and suitability for doctoral study. A personal interview (in person or via video conference) may be required.

EnglishScore: Proof of English Proficiency must be submitted by providing an official score report from one of the following: TOEFL (minimum score of 79 iBT or 550 PBT), IELTS (minimum score of 6.0), PTE (minimum score of 54), Duolingo (minimum score of 105), or by successful completion of the UNA English as a Second Language (ESL) Program.
Requirements: Admission to the Master of Professional Studies program requires: 1. a bachelor's degree from a regionally accredited institution. 2. an undergraduate GPA of 2.75 or higher on a 4.0 scale. 3. completion of the UNA Graduate Application. 4. official transcripts from all institutions attended. 5. a written statement of purpose describing the applicant's professional goals and reasons for pursuing the MPS degree. 6. three letters of recommendation. 7. an up-to-date résumé.
Description: The University of North Alabama's MPS in Broadcast Meteorology degree provides students a path for a career in broadcast meteorology by providing the coursework needed to obtain the National Weather Association's Seal of Approval. The degree can be earned either fully online or through hybrid delivery.

Accepted tests and minimum scores include: TOEFL iBT 61, TOEFL PBT 500, IELTS 5.5, PTE 46, Duolingo 95, or completion of ELS Level 112.
Requirements: The Certificate in Business program is open to non-business majors who want to broaden their knowledge in the fundamentals of business. The required curriculum includes six courses (18 hours) listed below. To enroll in these courses, a student must meet the prerequisite for each course, as listed in the catalog.
Description: The Certificate in Business is a 12 hour certificate designed for non-business majors. It provides an introductory foundation in the functional areas of business. Non-business majors who complete the certificate will enhance their chosen major with the business acumen that will increase their career success.
Accredidation: The UNA College of Business is an accredited member of AACSB International-The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business. The undergraduate and graduate programs are accredited.

An MBA, or equivalent business-focused Master's degree, from an AACSB-accredited or EQUIS-accredited institution.
At least 10 years of professional/managerial experience.

Department: College of Business and Technology
Description: The Executive Doctor of Business Administration (EDBA) program at the University of North Alabama is an applied professional doctoral degree program designed to equip senior business leaders with advanced knowledge and skills in key business functional areas. The program curriculum is designed to be completed in three years in a blended delivery format that is convenient for working professionals with a minimum of five years of progressive managerial or leadership experience. The EDBA curriculum has a strong focus on applied research to solve real-world business problems and is delivered by an outstanding team of experienced faculty.
Accredidation: AACSB-accredited

EnglishScore: All applicants whose native language is not English are required to demonstrate English proficiency. UNA will accept any of the following as proof of English proficiency: TOEFL minimum score of 79 (iBT) or 550 (PBT), IELTS minimum overall band score of 6.0, PTE Academic minimum score of 54, Duolingo minimum score of 110, or successful completion of ELS Level 112.
Requirements: A master's degree in a business-related discipline from an accredited institution. A minimum of seven years of professional and/or teaching experience, with a minimum of three years of mid- to upper-level management experience preferred. A grade point average (GPA) of 3.0 or higher (on a 4.0 scale) on all previous graduate coursework. Applicants must submit a current professional resume, a statement of purpose, and an official transcript from all previously attended colleges and universities. Three professional letters of reference are required for a complete application. The GMAT or GRE is not required for admission. The admissions committee will conduct an interview with all qualified applicants.
Description: The Executive Doctorate of Business Administration (EDBA) at the University of North Alabama is a professional doctoral program for executives and senior managers who want to advance into the highest levels of their organizations. Our program is a unique blend of rigor and relevance, and the hybrid format provides the necessary flexibility for working professionals to balance work, life, and school commitments. This three-year, 60 credit hour cohort model program will provide you with the skills and expertise needed to drive organizational change through evidence-based decision-making. Students can select from various focus areas to develop specialized knowledge and skills.
Accredidation: The UNA Sanders College of Business and Technology is accredited by AACSB International—The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of business.

EnglishScore: Applicants whose native language is not English must submit proof of English proficiency by providing an official score report from TOEFL, IELTS, PTE, or Duolingo. The minimum acceptable scores for admission are as follows: Internet-based TOEFL (iBT): 79, IELTS: 6.0, PTE Academic: 54, Duolingo: 110.
Requirements:
To be considered for admission to the Executive Doctorate in Business Administration (EDBA) program, applicants must submit the following:

*   Completed Application
*   Master's Degree (any discipline) from a regionally accredited university.
*   Official Transcripts from ALL universities attended (graduate and undergraduate)
*   Current Résumé
*   Statement of Purpose
*   Two Letters of Recommendation
*   A minimum of eight years of progressive management and/or leadership experience. Senior-level management and/or leadership experience is preferred.
*   A personal interview with the EDBA Admissions Committee will be required for applicants that are identified as potential candidates.
*   International students must meet UNA's international admission requirements.
Department: College of Business and Technology
Description: The Executive Doctor of Business Administration (EDBA) is a professional doctoral program for executives and senior managers who want to address business practice challenges through applied research. The program emphasizes the development of advanced critical thinking and research skills and their application to real-world business problems. The program will offer concentrations in specific areas of business to equip senior managers with the background needed to address complex organizational issues. The program is a hybrid program with students coming to campus three times a semester for a Friday/Saturday residency.
Accredidation: The Sanders College of Business and Technology is accredited by AACSB International, which represents the highest standard of achievement for business schools worldwide. Less than 5% of business schools worldwide have earned this prestigious designation.

EnglishScore: For international students, a TOEFL score of at least 79 (iBT) or IELTS score of at least 6.0 is required.
Requirements:
Admission to the Executive Doctor of Business Administration (EDBA) program is limited and competitive. Successful applicants must meet the following minimum requirements:

- A master’s degree in business or a related field from a regionally accredited institution, or its equivalent, from a foreign institution.
- A minimum of five years of significant managerial or leadership experience that demonstrates increasing levels of responsibility.
- A complete application submitted to the Office of Graduate Admissions, including:
    - Completed online application for admission and a non-refundable application fee.
    - Official transcripts from all universities attended.
    - A current resume.
    - Three professional letters of recommendation that address the applicant’s professional accomplishments and potential for success in a rigorous doctoral program.
    - A statement of purpose (approximately 1,500 words) that describes the applicant’s motivation for pursuing the EDBA, long-term professional goals, and a potential research topic.
    - An interview with the Director of the EDBA program.
- International applicants are required to submit a TOEFL, IELTS, or PTE score if the master’s degree was not from a US university.
Department: College of Business and Technology
Description: The University of North Alabama Executive Doctor of Business Administration (EDBA) is a professional doctoral program designed for working executives and senior managers who desire to become thought-leaders at their organizations. Our blended EDBA program offers executives a doctoral degree that is both rigorous and relevant. The program allows students to learn the essential skills and complex concepts to create a new vision for their organization’s future. The EDBA program provides a flexible path to a doctoral degree without disrupting personal and professional commitments. The program allows students to gain the expertise to make significant contributions to both business practice and theory. The EDBA program is designed to enhance executive capacity for undertaking applied research and to ensure graduates can manage organizations of all kinds in a dynamic, global environment.
Accredidation: The College of Business and Technology at the University of North Alabama is accredited by AACSB International – The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business.

EnglishScore: For international applicants, one of the following standardized tests are accepted as evidence of English proficiency for admission to a graduate degree program: Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) iBT with a score of 79, Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) PBT with a score of 550, International English Language Testing System (IELTS) with a score of 6.0, Pearson Test of English (PTE) Academic with a score of 54, Duolingo English Test with a score of 105, or ELS Educational Services (ELS) Level 112.
Requirements:
A master’s degree in business or a related field from a regionally accredited institution.
A minimum GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale on all previous graduate coursework.
A minimum of three years of mid-to-senior level professional/managerial experience. Exceptions may be granted for applicants with exceptional academic backgrounds.
An online application and a $100 non-refundable application fee.
Official transcripts from all universities attended (undergraduate and graduate).
Three letters of recommendation.
A current resume or curriculum vitae (CV).
A personal statement of 500-750 words outlining the applicant’s personal and professional goals and how the EDBA program will help achieve those goals.
An interview (online or in person).
Department: College of Business and Technology
Description: The Executive Doctor of Business Administration (EDBA) is a professional doctoral program for executives and senior managers who want to solve the complex challenges facing business and society. The program curriculum is not concentration specific, but instead focuses on applied research to solve contemporary business problems within the context of the student’s career and industry. EDBA students gain advanced knowledge in the business disciplines, learn to apply relevant theories and methodologies to real-world business problems, and develop applied research and writing skills. This approach enables graduates to make significant contributions to the advancement of business knowledge and practice.
Accredidation: The Sanders College of Business and Technology is accredited by AACSB International, the premier global accrediting body for business schools. AACSB Accreditation is the hallmark of excellence in business education and has been earned by less than five percent of the world's business programs.

EnglishScore: A Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) score of 550 on the paper-based test or 213 on the computer-based test or 79 on the internet-based test; or a score of 6.5 on the International English Language Testing System (IELTS); or a minimum of level 112 in the ELS Language Centers Program are required.
Requirements: Undergraduate students at the University of North Alabama who have completed at least 75 undergraduate credit hours with a minimum overall GPA of 3.0 may apply for admission to the Accelerated Master’s Program (AMP). Admission to the AMP allows students to take up to 12 graduate credit hours that may be used to satisfy requirements for both the bachelor’s and master’s degrees. Admission to the AMP is not the same as admission to the graduate program. AMP students will apply to the graduate program after completion of their undergraduate degree. If all other graduate admission requirements are met, then the student is fully admitted to the graduate program.
Department: College of Business and Technology
Description: The Accelerated Master’s Program (AMP) in Business Administration allows qualified UNA undergraduate students to begin their Master of Business Administration (MBA) graduate course work during their senior year. A student may take up to 9 hours of graduate courses during the senior year which may be applied to one of the ten concentrations offered in the traditional MBA program. By completing up to 9 hours of graduate course work prior to the completion of the baccalaureate degree, a student may earn an MBA degree in approximately 12 months after receiving the baccalaureate degree.
Accredidation: All undergraduate and graduate programs in the College of Business and Technology are accredited by AACSB International-The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business. The University of North Alabama is accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools Commission on Colleges (SACSCOC).

The UNA MBA is open to all students with a four-year baccalaureate degree from a regionally accredited college or university. No GMAT or GRE is required for admission. Admission can be granted in one of two ways:

Two letters of recommendation.
A current résumé.
A 250 word Statement of Purpose.

Alternative Admission
An earned bachelor’s degree from a regionally accredited institution with a minimum 2.0-2.49 cumulative GPA.
Three years of approved and documented professional work experience.
Official transcripts from all universities/colleges attended.
Two letters of recommendation.
A current résumé.
A 250 word Statement of Purpose.
Department: College of Business and Technology
Description: The University of North Alabama Master of Business Administration (MBA) degree is a graduate-level degree with a rich history. We’ve been a top choice for business professionals for more than 40 a years, having launched our program in 1975. Today we continue to grow and welcome students from across the globe. Our students join us on campus, online, or in a hybrid format. Our faculty bring real-world experience to the classroom to give you a competitive edge. Our MBA will teach you how to lead and manage in the global business environment. You can customize your MBA to align with your career goals, and with nine concentrations, you have a variety of choices. From Accounting to Information Systems to Sales, our MBA will help you reach your professional goals.
Accredidation: The UNA College of Business and Technology is accredited by AACSB International - The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business. AACSB is the premier agency for bachelor, master, and doctoral degree programs in business administration and accounting. AACSB International accreditation is the hallmark of excellence in management education.

An admission essay. A personal interview with the Director of the Executive MBA Program.
Department: College of Business and Technology
Description: The UNA Executive MBA is a cohort-based program designed for experienced professionals seeking to advance their careers by developing their management and leadership skills. This one-year online program can be completed in as little as 12 months with both online and hybrid learning options. The UNA Executive MBA offers a unique international study component that includes 8-10 days of international travel. Students visit a variety of global businesses and company executives while learning about the history, business practices, economics, and culture of a country. The Executive MBA is a part of our AACSB-accredited College of Business and Technology. In 2022, CEO Magazine named the UNA EMBA program as a Tier One program in their Global Executive MBA Rankings. Students in the program progress through the same sequence of courses as their cohort.
Accredidation: The Executive MBA is a part of our AACSB-accredited College of Business and Technology.

Description: The Business Analytics concentration will give students the skills and knowledge to turn data into actionable insights for better business decision-making. Students will gain experience with descriptive, predictive, and prescriptive analytics using a variety of statistical and analytical tools. Students learn to utilize data visualization, statistical and machine learning modeling, and optimization to address business problems across a wide variety of industries including finance, marketing, healthcare, and manufacturing. UNA’s Business Analytics MBA concentration will help prepare students to take certification exams such as the Certified Analytics Professional (CAP) exam.
Accredidation: The Steele-Cobb College of Business and Technology is accredited by AACSB International.
ScholarshipType: Graduate Assistant Scholarship, Graduate Dean's Scholarship

EnglishScore: International applicants must demonstrate English proficiency with one of the following minimum scores: TOEFL iBT 79, IELTS 6.0, PTE 54, or Duolingo 110. Completion of ELS Level 112 or UNA's English as a Second Language Program also satisfies the requirement. The requirement may be waived for applicants who have earned a degree from a regionally accredited U.S. institution or a recognized university in a country where English is the primary language.
Requirements:
Applicants for admission to the M.S. in Business Technology must meet the following criteria:
- Completed Application for Graduate Admission
- Official transcripts from all universities and colleges attended sent directly to the Office of Graduate Admissions
- A current résumé
- If an applicant meets one of the following criteria, the GMAT/GRE requirement is waived:
  - An undergraduate degree from a regionally-accredited university or college with a cumulative GPA of 3.0 or higher.
  - An undergraduate degree from a regionally-accredited university or college with a cumulative GPA of 2.75 or higher AND three years of relevant, professional work experience.
  - An awarded graduate degree from a regionally-accredited university.
- Applicants who do not meet one of the criteria above must submit official scores for the Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT) or Graduate Record Examination (GRE) that are less than five years old.
- To be considered for unconditional admission, an applicant must have a score of 450 or higher on the GMAT, or a score of 290 or higher on the GRE, and meet one of the following criteria:
  - An undergraduate degree from a regionally-accredited university or college with a cumulative GPA of 2.75 or higher.
  - An undergraduate degree from a regionally-accredited university or college with a cumulative GPA of 2.5 or higher and three years of professional work experience.
Department: College of Business and Technology
Description: The Master of Science in Business Technology (MSBT), offered exclusively online, is a 30-hour program designed to prepare students for technical careers in business. In this program, students will learn to apply information technology to solve business problems. The program has been developed by faculty with real-world experience and is designed to provide students with the knowledge, skills, and abilities needed to obtain employment in the information technology field. The MSBT program offers two concentrations: Business Analytics and Information Systems.
Accredidation: The College of Business and Technology at the University of North Alabama is accredited by AACSB International.

ProgramName: Cellular Physiology and Molecular Biophysics PhD

EnglishScore: Students must demonstrate proficiency in English through one of the following: Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) with a minimum score of 79 (Internet-based); International English Language Testing System (IELTS) with a minimum score of 6.0; Pearson Test of English (PTE) Academic with a score of 54; Duolingo English Test with a minimum score of 110; Graduation from ELS Language Center's Level 112 of the English for Academic Purposes Program; Graduation from a U.S. high school, college, or university; or Citizenship in a country where English is the official language.
Requirements: Complete the application for admission to the Graduate School. Submit a current resume. Submit a letter of application to the program addressing personal and professional qualifications and aspirations relevant to the counseling profession. Submit official transcripts from all institutions attended. A minimum undergraduate GPA of 2.75 on a 4.0 scale is required for Unconditional Admission. Submit names and email addresses for three professional/academic references who can address the applicant's potential for success in the counseling profession. References will be prompted to complete a recommendation form. Submit a score from the Miller Analogies Test (MAT) or the Graduate Record Exam (GRE-Verbal and Quantitative). Applicants meeting all of the above admission requirements will be invited for a personal interview with faculty in the Counselor Education program.
Description: The 60-semester hour Master of Arts degree in Clinical Mental Health Counseling prepares graduates for employment in a variety of public and private human service agencies including mental health centers, hospitals, substance abuse treatment facilities, correctional facilities, family counseling centers, and pastoral counseling settings. Graduates are prepared to apply for licensure as a Licensed Professional Counselor (LPC) in Alabama and other states.
Accredidation: The Clinical Mental Health Counseling program at UNA is accredited by the Council for Accreditation of Counseling and Related Educational Programs (CACREP).

ProgramName: Data Analytics and Program Evaluation MS Online
EnglishScore: Applicants whose native language is not English must submit evidence of English proficiency. Accepted tests include TOEFL iBT with a minimum score of 79, IELTS with a minimum score of 6.0, PTE with a minimum score of 54, or Duolingo English Test (DET) with a minimum score of 110.
Requirements: An official transcript from the college or university that awarded the baccalaureate degree and official transcripts from all colleges and universities attended. Submit a score from one of the following tests: GRE (verbal and quantitative sections), MAT, or GMAT. The test score must be no older than five years from the date of the examination. The GMAT, GRE and MAT requirement is temporarily waived through Fall 2024 for students with a 3.0 or higher cumulative GPA on their conferred bachelor's degree. Submit a Statement of Purpose. Submit three letters of recommendation. Submit a resume/vitae. Submit a writing sample. Have a minimum undergraduate GPA of 2.50 for unconditional admission.
Department: College of Education and Human Sciences
Description: The Master of Science in Education with a major in Data Analytics and Program Evaluation is designed to prepare educators and other professionals for careers that require expertise in data analysis, assessment, research, and program evaluation. The 30-hour program is designed for students from a variety of professional backgrounds, including but not limited to, P-12 education, higher education, healthcare, social services, military, and business.

ProgramName: Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP): Advanced Practice
EnglishScore: Evidence of English proficiency is required for students whose native language is not English. UNA requires one of the following for admission: TOEFL score of 79 (IBT), 550 (PBT) or 213 (CBT), or above; IELTS score of 6.0 or above; PTE score of 54 or above; Duolingo English Test score of 100 or above; or successful completion of ELS Language Center's level 112.
Requirements:
Application for admission to the Graduate School.
Bachelor of Science in Nursing degree from a regionally accredited institution and a nationally accredited nursing program (ACEN or CCNE).
Current unencumbered registered nurse license in the United States.
Minimum undergraduate grade point average of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale.
Official transcripts from all colleges/universities attended.
A current resume or curriculum vitae.
Goal Statement. The goal statement should be a maximum of 500 words describing your reasons for pursuing the DNP, your short and long-term professional goals, and how you see yourself as a DNP-prepared nurse.
Three letters of recommendation. Recommendations should be from individuals who can attest to your potential for success in a graduate program (examples include: current or former professors, current or former supervisors, and other professional colleagues).
Completion of an undergraduate or graduate statistics course with a grade of C or better.
Completion of an undergraduate or graduate research course with a grade of C or better.
Completion of an undergraduate or graduate physical assessment course with a grade of C or better.
Successful interview with DNP faculty.
Department: Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions
Description: UNA's BSN-DNP program prepares nurses for advanced practice and for leadership roles as clinical scholars. The curriculum is delivered in an online format to provide flexibility for working students. On-campus intensives are required each semester to provide opportunities for students to engage with faculty and colleagues and demonstrate specific skills and competencies. Clinical hours are completed in the student's own community. Students are prepared to sit for national certification in their specialty area upon graduation.
Accredidation: The baccalaureate degree program in nursing, master's degree program in nursing, and Doctor of Nursing Practice program at the University of North Alabama are accredited by the Commission on Collegiate Nursing Education (http://www.ccneaccreditation.org).

ProgramName: Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP): Population Health
Requirements:
Application to the Office of Graduate Admissions at UNA. The application can be found at www.una.edu/graduate.
Minimum GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale on all graduate coursework.
Current unencumbered RN license in the state where clinical experiences will occur.
Current certification as a nurse practitioner or clinical nurse specialist from a national certifying body.
Master of Science in Nursing (MSN) or a Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP) from a nationally accredited nursing program (Accreditation Commission for Education in Nursing [ACEN] or Commission on Collegiate Nursing Education [CCNE]).
Submission of the following documents to the Office of Graduate Admissions:
Official transcripts from all colleges/universities attended.
Verification of clinical hours from previous graduate nursing program (must meet the 1000-hour requirement post-BSN).
Current resume or curriculum vitae (CV).
Professional portfolio to include:
A written statement describing professional goals and how the DNP degree will help to achieve those goals.
A scholarly paper from a previous graduate program.
Evidence of scholarship (e.g., publications, presentations, grant funding, etc.).
Evidence of professional service.
Three letters of professional reference attesting to the applicant’s potential for doctoral study.
Interview with graduate nursing faculty.
Department: Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions
Description:
The Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP) degree is a practice-focused doctorate designed to prepare experts in specialized advanced nursing practice. The DNP curriculum at the University of North Alabama Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions focuses on providing the skills and knowledge to enable graduates to provide the most advanced level of nursing care for individuals, families, and communities. The DNP program provides a curriculum that is consistent with professional standards and is designed to prepare graduates to:

Utilize advanced levels of clinical judgment, systems thinking, and accountability in designing, delivering, and evaluating evidence-based care to improve patient outcomes.
Critically appraise and synthesize evidence for the development of practice guidelines and projects.
Assume complex leadership roles to advance clinical practice and healthcare.
Advocate for social justice, equity, and ethical policies in healthcare.
Employ information systems and technology in the delivery of healthcare.
Collaborate with interprofessional teams to analyze and improve health outcomes.

Our Population Health focus prepares our graduates for leadership roles in a variety of settings. Students learn how to analyze data and evidence to improve patient outcomes and to design, implement, and evaluate new models of care delivery.
Accredidation: The Doctor of Nursing Practice program at the University of North Alabama are accredited by the Commission on Collegiate Nursing Education (http://www.ccneaccreditation.org).

ProgramName: Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP): Educational Leadership
EnglishScore: Students from non-English speaking countries must submit an official score report from one of the following exams: TOEFL: 79 iBT or 550 PBT; IELTS: 6.0; PTE Academic: 54; Duolingo: 100; ELS: Level 112 with a 2.5 GPA.
Department: Anderson College of Nursing and Health Professions

EnglishScore: All applicants whose native language is not English must submit evidence of English proficiency. This can be demonstrated by one of the following: TOEFL minimum score of 79 iBT (internet based test) or 550 PBT (paper based test). IELTS minimum score of 6.0.
